messages.content:
Here are two solid, but very different, options that Lily can book for her one-way rental from Philadelphia International Airport (PHL) to Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport (DCA).

────────────────────────────────────────
1) Intermediate-size – Nissan Sentra (Dollar Rent-A-Car)
────────────────────────────────────────
Quick profile
• Size / class  Intermediate sedan  
• Seats / doors 5 seats, 4 doors (listed internally as “2-door” but fleet is normally 4-door)  
• Luggage   Up to 2–3 mid-size suitcases  
• Transmission Automatic     • A/C Yes  
• Mileage   Unlimited  
• Fuel policy  Return with the same fuel level (“Like-for-like”)  

Price & payment
• Pay-now amount (charged when you book)……………US $ 300.98  
• Mandatory taxes & fees already included in that price  
  – Airport concession fee US $ 8.33  
  – City / county / state taxes about US $ 9.34 total  
  – One-way fee US $ 75 (already rolled in)  
• Approx. “drive-away” total (nothing else due at the counter except deposit)…………US $ 394.32  
• Security-deposit hold at pick-up (credit card)……US $ 273.98–684.96*  
  (*figure may vary by card type; Dollar shows the maximum hold.)  

What’s included
✓ Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
✓ Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)  
✓ Theft Protection  
✓ Third-Party Liability  
✓ Unlimited mileage  

Optional extras (pay at counter, prices per rental)  
• Additional driver US $ 94.50  
• Baby / child / booster seat US $ 97.93 each (max 2)  

Optional protection add-on  
Extra Cover (zero-excess, covers gaps in CDW)……US $ 57.73 — can be added during booking and cancelled free of charge.

Pick-up / drop-off logistics
PHL – From baggage claim, walk to Zone 2 and take the Dollar shuttle (3-4 min ride).  
DCA – Car returned to Dollar off-airport lot; shuttle takes you to terminal.  

Pros & cons at a glance
+ Comfortable for highway driving between cities  
+ Largest trunk and rear-seat space of the two options  
+ Only ~US $16 more than the economy car after fees  
– Slightly higher fuel consumption vs. the smaller Spark  
– Same sizeable security-deposit hold as the cheaper class  

────────────────────────────────────────
2) Economy-size – Chevrolet Spark (Dollar Rent-A-Car)
────────────────────────────────────────
Quick profile
• Size / class  Economy hatchback  
• Seats / doors 4 seats, 4 doors (fleet‐standard)  
• Luggage   1 large + 1 small case (tight but doable)  
• Transmission Automatic     • A/C Yes  
• Mileage   Unlimited  
• Fuel policy  Return same level (“Like-for-like”)  

Price & payment
• Pay-now amount (charged when you book)……………US $ 285.73  
• Mandatory taxes & fees already included  
  – Airport concession fee US $ 8.33  
  – City / county / state taxes about US $ 9.34 total  
  – One-way fee US $ 75 (already rolled in)  
• Approx. “drive-away” total……………………………………US $ 379.07  
• Security-deposit hold at pick-up……………………US $ 273.98–684.96  

What’s included
✓ Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
✓ Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)  
✓ Theft Protection  
✓ Third-Party Liability  
✓ Unlimited mileage  

Optional extras (same prices as above)  
• Additional driver US $ 94.50  
• Baby / child / booster seat US $ 97.93 each  

Optional protection add-on  
Extra Cover (zero-excess)………………………………US $ 57.73  

Pick-up / drop-off logistics
Identical shuttles and depot locations as the Sentra (Dollar shuttle at both airports).  

Pros & cons at a glance
+ Lowest upfront cost  
+ Easy to park in Washington D.C. streets & garages  
+ Excellent fuel economy  
– Cabin & trunk space much tighter; fine for 1–2 people, cozy for 3, impractical for 4 + luggage  
– Same deposit as the larger car, so cash-flow advantage is minimal  

────────────────────────────────────────
Key things Lily should remember at pick-up
1. Main driver’s NAME credit card is mandatory (debit cards not accepted for deposit).  
2. Driver’s licence + passport/ID must match reservation.  
3. Dollar allows free cancellation up to 48 h before 30 Nov 09:00; after that the first-day charge applies.  
4. Return fuel to the agreed level to avoid refuelling charges.  
5. One-way drop fee (US $ 75) is already prepaid; nothing extra is due for dropping in D.C.  

────────────────────────────────────────
Which to choose?
• Travelling light (1–2 people, minimal luggage) or prioritising price & easy parking → Chevrolet Spark.  
• Want more comfort on the 2-hour Philly-to-D.C. drive, or carrying several bags → Nissan Sentra.  

Both cars can be booked immediately with free cancellation, giving Lily flexibility if her plans change.

Here are two solid, but distinctly different, one-way rentals that match Lily’s exact schedule (Denver DEN pick-up 20 Dec 2024 10:00 → Salt Lake City SLC return 27 Dec 2024 15:00).

────────────────────────────────────────
1) Intermediate SEDAN – Chevrolet Cruze (Avis)
────────────────────────────────────────
Total price (pay-now): US $ 684.06  ≈ US $ 85.50 / day  
Drive-away figure already includes all mandatory taxes & fees.

Vehicle basics
• 5 seats ‒ 2 / 4 doors  
• Luggage: 1 large + 1 small suitcase  
• Transmission: Automatic   • Air-con: Yes  
• Fuel type: Petrol (return “like-for-like”)  
• Mileage: Unlimited

Supplier, depot & logistics
• Supplier: Avis   – Customer rating at DEN: 6.6 / 10 (“OK”, 240 reviews)  
• Pick-up: Shuttle-bus counter.  After baggage claim walk to Shuttle Stand #4; 5-min ride to Avis lot.  
• Return: In-terminal car-rental garage at SLC – follow Rental-Car signs on Terminal Drive.  
• Security deposit/credit-card hold: US $ 250 (main driver’s credit card, physical card required).

What’s already included
✓ Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
✓ Collision-Damage Waiver (CDW) with zero excess  
✓ Theft cover & Third-party liability  
✓ Unlimited mileage  
✓ Amendments with no agency fee

Optional extras (pay at desk, subject to availability)
‣ Additional driver: US $ 65 per rental  
‣ Child/booster/baby seats: US $ 87 each  
‣ GPS: US $ 135.92 per rental  

Typical running costs
• Fuel economy for a Cruze is ~32 mpg highway. Current Utah/Colorado petrol is ~US $ 3.70 / gal (Nov 2023 prices).  
• Toll roads: E-470 around DEN and I-25 Express Lanes use transponders; Avis passes tolls plus an admin fee (~US $ 5.95 / day, max 29.75) if triggered.

Good for: Couples or small families that travel light, want sedan handling & lowest total cost.

────────────────────────────────────────
2) Intermediate SUV – Ford Escape (Avis)
────────────────────────────────────────
Total price (pay-now): US $ 821.09  ≈ US $ 102.60 / day

Vehicle basics
• 5 seats ‒ 4 doors  
• Luggage: up to 3 large cases (rear seats up)  
• Higher driving position, optional AWD on most fleet Escapes  
• Transmission: Automatic   • Air-con: Yes  
• Fuel type: Petrol (return “like-for-like”)  
• Mileage: Unlimited

Supplier, depot & logistics
• Same Avis shuttle pick-up at DEN; same in-terminal drop-off bay at SLC.  
• Supplier rating identical (6.6 / 10).  
• Security deposit: US $ 250 on a credit card.

What’s already included
✓ Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
✓ CDW, Theft & TPL cover  
✓ Unlimited mileage  
✓ Amendments with no fee

Optional extras & fees
(identical price list to the Cruze – Additional driver 65 USD, seats 87 USD, GPS 135.92 USD, etc.)

Typical running costs
• Real-world fuel economy ~28 mpg highway; roughly 10–15 % higher fuel spend than the Cruze.  
• Same toll-road rules apply.

Good for: Travellers who need extra cargo space or prefer SUV ride height, willing to pay ~US $ 137 more for the week.

────────────────────────────────────────
Side-by-side snapshot
                Chevy Cruze (Sedan)   |  Ford Escape (SUV)
————————————————————————————————————————
Price (8 days)     US $ 684               |  US $ 821
Seats / doors      5 / 4                 |  5 / 4
Suitcases          1 L + 1 S             |  up to 3 L
Ground-clearance   Low (sedan)           |  Higher (light off-road OK)
Per-day fuel use*  ~3.1 gal / 50 mi      |  ~3.6 gal / 50 mi
*estimates at 32 mpg vs 28 mpg highway.

Both cars:
• Automatic, A/C, unlimited miles, “return same fuel”.  
• Free cancellation up to 18 Dec 10:00.  
• Main driver must be 25 + yrs with full licence & credit card in own name.  
• One-way fee is already embedded in the quoted totals—no surprise drop-charge.

How Lily can book
1. Choose vehicle class above.  
2. Have driver’s licence & credit card (same name) ready.  Secondary IDs (passport or utility bill) sometimes requested.  
3. Consider locking in “Total Protection” (≈ US $ 65.97) if she prefers zero-hassle cover beyond CDW.  
4. At DEN follow Avis shuttle instructions; at SLC simply park in the signed Avis return row and hand keys to the agent.

That’s it—two clear choices with all the key numbers, terms and practical details so Lily can decide quickly. Safe travels!

messages.content:
Here are two solid – and noticeably different – options that match Lily’s one-way itinerary (PHX ➜ TUS, 20 Dec 2024 11:00 → 28 Dec 2024 14:00).  Both are offered by Hertz and include the mandatory one-way fee in the price shown.

────────────────────────────
1.  Intermediate – Toyota Corolla (Automatic)
────────────────────────────
Class / size            Intermediate sedan  
Typical model           Toyota Corolla (4-door)  
Seats / doors           5 seats / 4 doors  
Luggage                 1 large + 1 small suitcase (boot ≈ 370 L)  
Transmission / fuel     Automatic / petrol; “Like-for-like” fuel policy  
Air-conditioning        Yes  
Mileage                 Unlimited  
Supplier rating         8.7 / 10 (“Fabulous” – 103 PHX reviews)  
Pick-up location        Hertz desk – Rental-Car Center, Phoenix Sky Harbor  
Drop-off location       Hertz shuttle, Tucson Int’l Airport  
Freebies                • Free amendments & cancellation (to 48 h before)  

PRICE BREAK-DOWN (all mandatory charges)  
 Pay-now amount (car + taxes)           US$ 483.32  
 One-way fee (already in drive-away)    US$  96.33  
 ────────────────────────────────────────────────  
 Drive-away total (what Lily will actually pay) US$ 579.65  

Deposits / excesses  
 • Refundable security hold on credit card at pick-up  …US$ 0-684.96  
 • Damage excess (CDW) & theft excess………………US$ 0 (covered)  

Included protection  
 ✓ Collision-Damage-Waiver (CDW)  
 ✓ Theft protection  
 ✓ Third-party liability  
Option to add “Total Protection” (zero excess, windscreens, towing, etc.) for ≈ US$ 74.22 for the whole rental.

Extras on request (pay at counter)  
 • Additional driver US$ 121.50 per rental  
 • Baby/child/booster seat US$ 91 each per rental  

Why choose it?  
More cabin room than an Economy, better for 4-5 adults or bulkier bags, modest bump in price (≈ US$ 15/day more than the Veloster once the one-way fee is included).

────────────────────────────
2.  Economy – Hyundai Veloster (Automatic)
────────────────────────────
Class / size            Economy 3-door hatch (with rear “half-door”)  
Typical model           Hyundai Veloster (4 doors* incl. hatch)  
Seats / doors           4 seats / 4 doors*  
Luggage                 1 large + 1 small suitcase (boot ≈ 320 L)  
Transmission / fuel     Automatic / petrol; “Like-for-like” fuel policy  
Air-conditioning        Yes  
Mileage                 Unlimited  
Supplier rating         8.7 / 10 (same Hertz counter & service)  
Pick-up / drop-off      Identical venues as above (shuttle to PHX RCC, shuttle return at TUS)  
Freebies                • Free amendments & cancellation (to 48 h before)  

PRICE BREAK-DOWN  
 Pay-now amount (car + taxes)           US$ 440.94  
 One-way fee (already in drive-away)    US$  96.33  
 ────────────────────────────────────────────────  
 Drive-away total (what Lily will actually pay) US$ 537.27  

Deposits / excesses  
 • Refundable security hold…………………US$ 0-684.96  
 • Damage / theft excess…………………US$ 0  

Included protection & optional extras: identical to the Corolla.

Why choose it?  
Cheaper up-front (≈ US$ 483 vs 579 total); nimbler around town and slightly better fuel economy.  Downsides: one less seat, tighter rear access, smaller boot.

────────────────────────────
Key pick-up details & rental tips
────────────────────────────
• At PHX, follow airport signs to “Rental Car Shuttle” outside baggage claim – the blue/green buses run every 5 min, 5-min ride to the Hertz counter.  
• Bring:  (a) Lily’s driver licence,  (b) a major credit card in her own name (for the US$ 0-684 hold),  (c) passport/ID if the licence is non-US.  
• Hertz allows a 29-minute grace period on return; arriving much later than 14:00 may incur an extra day.  
• Fuel-return “Like-for-like”: refuel to the same level shown on the pick-up slip to avoid refuelling charges.  
• Unlimited mileage means she can explore side trips (Sedona, Saguaro NP, etc.) at no extra cost.  
• One-way fee (US$ 96.33) is already built in; there are no drop-off surcharges beyond what is listed.  

────────────────────────────
Quick comparison at a glance
────────────────────────────
                Corolla (Intermediate)   |   Veloster (Economy)  
─────────────────────────────────────────|─────────────────────────
Total cost (8-day drive-away)            | US$ 579.65 | US$ 537.27  
Daily cost (approx.)                     | US$ 72     | US$ 67  
Seats / luggage                          | 5 / 2 bags | 4 / 2 bags  
Cabin space / comfort                    | ★★★☆       | ★★☆  
Fuel economy (real-world)                | 34 mpg     | 37 mpg  
Ease of parking                          | ★★☆        | ★★★☆  
Best for                                 | 3-5 people, longer drives | 1-3 people, city use  

If Lily values space and doesn’t mind an extra ~US$ 42 overall, the Corolla is the safer, roomier pick.  If budget and manoeuvrability matter most, the Veloster will do the job nicely.

(that's C$1,488.57, i.e. 367% more than the basic rental prepaid through rentalcars.com!!! (that excessive rental cost noted above is exclusive of the 8.10% VAT, and the "Premium Location Fee" of 20%, which was not noted on the rentalcars.com agreement.  - not holding it against you....but SixT certainly lives up to its worldwide reputation as untrust-worthy rental company.
When they emailed me a request to rate their service, I told them loud and clear that unless they amend the final charge upon return of the vehicle, I'll see them in court.
The credit-card pre-authorization (Security Deposit) of CHF 1,463.56 was cancelled/withdrawn two days before end of rental, but to this day, I don't know what they debited to my credit-card, as there is still no Sixt debit showing on my Visa account.
That said, I had also purchased a CDW through rentalcoverage.com, the confirmation of which I showed to the SixT agent upon pickup (she did not take the details), but upon return of the vehicle they claimed that I damaged the rear-left wheel rim (5-10 cms down to primer); when I told the receiving agent that I a) have CDW coverage and b) had taken photos at time of pickup, which clearly shows the pre-existing damage, she noted it on the Return-Receipt, but I am now being hounded by the SixT-Damage dept. (As I'm still travelling, I have had no time to respond, and frankly see no reason why I should respond to that department.
Last, but not least, Sixt's Diamond member should not be permitted to push through a line of 12 people waiting to be served, when there is no dedicated Diamond-Member counter.
Decency toward the common-mortals is sorely lacking at Sixt!
PS: I've rented cars through rentalcars.com previously and everything went without a hitch....s

Here’s a snapshot of the first (and currently “Recommended – best first”) offer returned for your dates and one-way itinerary Madrid-to-Barcelona.  It should give you a good feel for the sort of car, costs, supplier quality and real-world feedback you can expect.  (All prices and fees are taken directly from the live quote supplied by the system.)

────────────────────────────────────────
1) Vehicle & Rental Details
────────────────────────────────────────
• Car class / model shown: Mini – Citroën C1 (or similar)  
• Doors / seats: 2 doors / 4 seats  
• Luggage: 1 big + 1 small suitcase  
• Transmission: Manual  • Air-conditioning: Yes  
• Fuel policy: “Like-for-like” (return with same level you collect)  
• Mileage allowance: 1 200 km per rental (≈150 km per day).  Extra km €0.15–0.23 each.  
• Free cancellation: Up to 48 h before pick-up  
• Pick-up depot: Madrid-Barajas Airport (in-terminal, T1/T4 rental area)  
• Drop-off depot: Barcelona-El Prat Airport (in-terminal, Terminals 1 & 2)

Indicative price (all in, for 15–22 Dec 2024):
‣ Pay-now rental charge:            US$ 146.87  
‣ One-way fee (Madrid→Barcelona):  US$ 172.40  (already included above)  
‣ Estimated drive-away total:       US$ 319.27  

Other money matters to note
• Refundable security deposit:  €1 100 (held on card)  
• Damage-excess liability:       €2 300 (amount you could be charged if the car is damaged or stolen unless you buy extra cover)  
• Admin fee if damage occurs:    €50  
• Fuel-deposit / valet fees may be pre-authorised if the tank isn’t returned at the same level.

Optional extras (pay at counter, per rental):
– Additional driver  €80 – Baby/child/booster seat  €96 each – GPS  €63.60

────────────────────────────────────────
2) Supplier Quality – Goldcar @ Madrid-Barajas
────────────────────────────────────────
Overall rating: 7.3 / 10  (“Good”) based on 3 983 customer reviews

Break-down of the score
• Car cleanliness ....................... 8.0  
• Drop-off speed ........................ 8.9  
• Helpfulness of staff .................. 7.2  
• Pick-up speed ......................... 7.1  
• Value for money ....................... 6.5  

────────────────────────────────────────
3) Recent Customer Comments
────────────────────────────────────────
(Extracts from the most recent reviews in Oct 2024; spelling/punctuation kept as in source.)

1. Rating 7.7 – Family (23 Oct 2024)  
   + “Staff were good… car was in very good condition and really enjoyable to drive.”  
   – “Not much explanation of the car’s controls; would be tough for a first-timer.”

2. Rating 2.9 – Solo traveller (15 Oct 2024)  
   – “Told me I must have a credit card and couldn’t use a debit card unless I bought their full insurance.”

3. Rating 6.6 – Solo traveller (3 Oct 2024)  
   + “Pick up very close to arrivals.”  
   – “Wouldn’t accept my card unless I paid again for insurance I’d already bought elsewhere.”

4. Rating 3.7 – Solo traveller (1 Oct 2024 – review in Spanish)  
   – “No automatic cars available as booked, very long queue, car dirty outside.”

5. Rating 8.0 – Couple (24 Sept 2024)  
   + “Staff gave us an upgrade and unlimited mileage.”  
   – “Had to pay extra for insurance & later got unexpected mileage charge.”

────────────────────────────────────────
Is this car a good fit?

• PROS: Cheap headline rate; easy in-terminal collection; drop-off speed & cleanliness score high; free cancellation until two days before.  
• CONS: Low mileage cap (1 200 km – double-check your planned route); high excess & deposit; several reviews complain about upselling insurance / card requirements.

Tip: If you expect to exceed 1 200 km (Madrid → Barcelona via e.g. Valencia, Zaragoza & day trips could easily go over), look for an offer with “unlimited mileage”.  Also bring a true credit card in the main driver’s name, or be prepared to buy the supplier’s insurance on the spot.

Let me know if you’d like to see more vehicle options (e.g. automatic, estate, premium class, unlimited mileage, different suppliers) or have any other questions!

messages.content:
Here are the cars in your Frankfurt-to-Berlin search that explicitly list “Snow chains” among the bookable extras.  All prices shown are “drive-away” totals for the four-day rental (pick-up 10 Nov 2024 15:00, drop-off 14 Nov 2024 15:00).  The snow-chain fee is paid at the counter and is not yet included in the drive-away total; it is shown separately.

────────────────────────────────────
1.  MG MG5 (Compact, fully electric) • Sixt  
   • Transmission Automatic | Seats 5 | Doors 4 | A/C ✅  
   • Luggage 1 large + 1 small (manufacturer figure)  
   • Mileage 1 200 km total for the rental (≈ 300 km/day) – €0.36 / km thereafter  
   • Pick-up Frankfurt Hbf “Mietwagenzentrum” (train-station depot)  
   • Drop-off Berlin-Mitte (Hauptbahnhof)  
   • Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
   • Deposit €300 (credit card, refundable)  
   • Damage / theft excess €1 050  
   • Drive-away price US $ 405.21  
   • Snow-chain extra €67.96 (≈ US $ 73.84) for the rental  

────────────────────────────────────
2.  Volkswagen Polo (Economy) • Sixt  
   • Transmission Manual | Seats 5 | Doors 4 | A/C ✅  
   • Luggage 1 large + 1 small  
   • Mileage 1 200 km total (same over-mileage rate)  
   • Pick-up / drop-off depots Same as above  
   • Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
   • Deposit €300 | Excess €1 050  
   • Drive-away price US $ 391.83  
   • Snow-chain extra €67.96 (≈ US $ 73.84)

────────────────────────────────────
3.  Fiat 500 (Mini) • Sixt  
   • Transmission Manual | Seats 4 | Doors 2 | A/C ✅  
   • Luggage 1 large + 1 small  
   • Mileage 1 200 km total (same over-mileage rate)  
   • Pick-up / drop-off depots Same as above  
   • Free cancellation up to 48 h before pick-up  
   • Deposit €300 | Excess €1 050  
   • Drive-away price US $ 387.33  
   • Snow-chain extra €67.96 (≈ US $ 73.84)  
   • Special note Rental price already includes Germany’s winterisation fee.

────────────────────────────────────
Key points to keep in mind
• Snow-chains are optional extras: request them in the “Extras” step before you confirm the booking or add them at the counter (stock is limited to one set per car).  
• You’ll pay the snow-chain fee locally, on top of the drive-away amount shown above.  
• All three vehicles share the same pick-up and drop-off depots and the same mileage limit, deposit, and excess figures.  
• A credit card in the main driver’s name is mandatory at pick-up for the €300 security deposit.  
• If you plan to exceed 1 200 km (Frankfurt–Berlin–Frankfurt via motorway is ~1 100 km), factor in the €0.36 / km over-mileage charge or look for an “Unlimited kilometres” option in the results.

Tip Snow-chains are most useful in alpine or rural snowy roads.  For major highways between Frankfurt and Berlin winter tyres (already mandatory nationwide when conditions demand) will usually be enough—but if you’re heading to mountainous areas the chains are a good safety net.

   • Pick-up:  Paris – Gare du Nord (train-station desk)  
     ‑ Mon 25 Nov 2024, 13:00  
   • Drop-off:  Geneva Airport – French Sector (in-terminal)

       – “Baby seat” (rear-facing, up to ~9 kg / 20 lb)

   • Other child-extras also offered: child seat (9-18 kg) and booster (18-45 kg).

messages.content:
Here’s what is currently available for 10 Dec 2024 08:00 (Stockholm Train Station) → 12 Dec 2024 08:00 (Copenhagen Airport) that offers an optional Ski-rack extra.  
All three cars are supplied by Avis (customer rating 8.7/10, “Fabulous”).

────────────────────────────────────────
1. Ford Kuga  – Standard/Hybrid (Automatic)  
• Seats / Doors / Bags 5 / 4 / 2 big + 1 small  
• Unlimited mileage & air-con  
• Base rental price (pay-now) US $ 1 023.92  
• Ski-rack extra US $ 33.08 (per rental, pay-at-desk)  
• Refundable security hold ≈ SEK 4 500 (~US $ 425) on pickup  
• Damage/Theft excess SEK 9 500 (~US $ 898) unless you add insurance  
• Free cancellation up to 48 h before pickup  

────────────────────────────────────────
2. Seat Leon  – Compact (Manual)  
• Seats / Doors / Bags 5 / 5 / 1 big + 1 small  
• Unlimited mileage & air-con  
• Base rental price (pay-now) US $   994.37  
• Ski-rack extra US $ 33.08 (per rental, pay-at-desk)  
• Refundable security hold ≈ SEK 4 500 (~US $ 425)  
• Damage/Theft excess SEK 9 500 (~US $ 898)  
• Free cancellation up to 48 h before pickup  

────────────────────────────────────────
3. Peugeot 5008  – Intermediate 7-seater (Automatic)  
• Seats / Doors / Bags 7 / 4 / 3 big  
• Unlimited mileage & air-con  
• Base rental price (pay-now) US $ 4 373.79  
• Ski-rack extra US $ 33.08 (per rental, pay-at-desk)  
• Refundable security hold ≈ SEK 4 500 (~US $ 425)  
• Damage/Theft excess SEK 9 500 (~US $ 898)  
• Free cancellation up to 48 h before pickup  

Pick-up & Drop-off depots (all cars)  
• Pickup Stockholm Central Train Station – 92 Klarabergsviadukten, 111 64 Stockholm  
• Drop-off Copenhagen Airport – Car Rental Centre, Lufthavnsboulevarden 2, 2770 København  

Ski-rack pricing is per vehicle (1 rack max).  Add it during the “Extras” step or at the counter.  Prices and availability can change, so reserve early if one of these fits your plan.
